OL,3,CParents of girl who died in kitchen
OL,4,Cincident serving 'life sentences',
OL,5,Cjury told
OL,7,FThe prosecution claims he picked up a
OL,8,Fknife and stabbed her in the chest
OL,9,Fafter the family indulged in horseplay
OL,10,Fwhile her mother Sarah Hall, Vickers'
OL,11,Fpartner of 27 years, cooked spaghetti
OL,12,Fbolognese.
OL,14,FThey say he has changed his account of
OL,15,Fwhat happened, having claimed he
OL,16,Faccidentally threw a knife at her,
OL,17,Fwith an expert pathologist saying that
OL,18,Fthe weapon must have been held due to
OL,19,Fthe nature of the wound.
